About the Project

Smart Dermatology is a web application designed to assist users in identifying potential skin conditions by analyzing uploaded images. Using advanced machine learning models, the application provides predictions to help users understand their skin health better.

This project aims to make dermatological insights more accessible and convenient for everyone, leveraging technology to bridge the gap between users and healthcare.

About the Dataset

The application uses the Skin Disease Classification Image Dataset, which is available on Kaggle. This dataset contains a diverse collection of images representing various skin conditions, enabling the training of machine learning models for accurate disease prediction.

Dataset Source: Kaggle - Skin Disease Classification Image Dataset
